The paper deals with the secrecy of a distributed-storage system for passwords, which involves information theory and cryptography. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves coding theory, which falls under cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper discusses a generalized model that is robust against disk failures, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
